1. Diffusion on the Spider Web

When heat spreads through metal, it follows the diffusion equation.

\frac{\partial u}{\partial t}=D\nabla^2 u

Where
	•	u = heat intensity
	•	D = diffusion constant
	•	\nabla^2 = Laplacian operator

The surprising thing: the same equation works on graphs.

Replace the spatial Laplacian with the graph Laplacian.

Meaning ideas spread through a knowledge graph exactly like heat spreads through metal.

Pantheon interpretation:

idea energy
     ↓
diffuses through conceptual web
     ↓
clusters form

Those clusters correspond to insight zones.

